a) Morse Code: It is method of transmitting information as a series of on-off tones, lights or any other means (which is timely tuned) that can be directly understood by a skilled listener or observer without special equipment.
   (Encodes 26 English letters A-Z, some non english letters, Digits, some special character and smaller set of procedural signals - source Wikipedia and other articles)
b) It was created by Samuel Morse and Alfred Vail back in 1830s, to transmit messages across telegraph wires.
